--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
THIRD-PARTY MODELS & DATASETS (attribution)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This project fetches and/or builds upon third-party models and datasets, each
governed by its own upstream license/terms. They are NOT covered by the
proprietary notice above; review and comply with each upstream license before
use or redistribution.

- GraphCodeBERT (microsoft/graphcodebert-base)
  Microsoft. Used as the base encoder for the vulnerability classifier.
  https://huggingface.co/microsoft/graphcodebert-base
  Ref: Guo et al., "GraphCodeBERT: Pre-training Code Representations with Data
  Flow" (ICLR 2021).

- Qwen2.5-Coder (Qwen / Alibaba Cloud)
  Used as the optional local Ollama explainer model (e.g. qwen2.5-coder:7b/14b/32b).
  https://huggingface.co/Qwen
  Subject to the applicable Qwen / Tongyi Qianwen license terms.

- BigVul (Big-Vul vulnerability dataset)
  Used as training/evaluation data for the vulnerability classifier.
  Ref: Fan et al., "A C/C++ Code Vulnerability Dataset with Code Changes and CVE
  Summaries" (MSR 2020). https://github.com/ZeoVan/MSR_20_Code_vulnerability_CSV_Dataset

All trademarks and model/dataset names are the property of their respective
owners.
